\left\Vert \frac{c'}{\lambda_1}z\right\Vert^2 < \Vert z \Vert^2
\begin{align} \Vert z \Vert^2 &=\sum |\langle z,\phi_i\rangle |^2 \\ &=\sum \frac 1 {\lambda_i^2}|\langle z,\lambda_i\phi_i\rangle |^2 \\ &=\sum \frac 1 {\lambda_i^2}|\langle z,L \phi_i\rangle |^2 \\ &=\sum \frac 1 {\lambda_i^2}|\langle L z,\phi_i\rangle |^2 \quad \text{since }L\text{ is self-adjoint,}\\ &=\sum \frac 1 {\lambda_i^2}|\langle c'z,\phi_i\rangle |^2 \\ &\leq \sum \frac 1 {\lambda_1^2}|\langle c'z,\phi_i\rangle |^2=\left\Vert \frac{c'}{\lambda_1}z\right\Vert^2.  \end {align}
\int \left|\frac{c'}{\lambda_1}z\right|^2\le \int \left|\frac{\alpha}{\lambda_1}z\right|^2 < \int |z|^2,
